                '<p>A company may need to increase its authorized capital for various business reasons \u2014 raising additional equity from new or existing investors, allotting shares to angel investors or venture capital funds, converting outstanding loans or debentures into equity, implementing Employee Stock Option Plans (ESOPs), issuing bonus shares to existing shareholders, or expanding the capital base for mergers and acquisitions. The increase requires an ordinary resolution of shareholders passed at a General Meeting and is subject to stamp duty payment as per the applicable state stamp duty rates.</p>',
